The most anticipated category of the Millennium Awards has finally revealed its contenders for the 2025 edition. This year's Album Of The Year race reflects a landscape of great diversity, bringing together rock icons, hip-hop giants, and global pop stars.

 The 2025 Nominees are:
 Debí Tirar Más Fotos – Bad Bunny; 
 Diamantes, Lágrimas e Rostos Para Esquecer – BK'; 
 Sable, Fable – Bon Iver; 
 Private Music – Deftones; 
 Who Believes in Angels? – Elton John & Brandi Carlile; 
 GNX – Kendrick Lamar; 
 Mayhem – Lady Gaga; 
 Chromakopia – Tyler, The Creator.

This year's lineup is defined by significant debuts in the main category. The band Deftones has earned their first-ever Album Of The Year nomination, a milestone shared this edition by Brazilian rapper BK', the visionary Tyler, The Creator, and the legendary partnership of Elton John & Brandi Carlile.

Among the returning names, stories of perseverance stand out. Lady Gaga secures her 4th nomination in this category, still chasing her first victory. Meanwhile, Bad Bunny and Bon Iver return for their second attempts: the Puerto Rican superstar was previously nominated in 2020 for 'YHLQMDLG', while the group led by Justin Vernon first competed in 2016 with '22, A Million'.

The ultimate veteran of the night is Kendrick Lamar. With 'GNX', the rapper reaches his 5th Album Of The Year nomination. Kendrick is the only nominee in the 2025 class who already holds the trophy, having won the category in 2017 with the landmark album 'DAMN.'
